{
  "texts": [
    "Their study focused on time window pricing and its influence on customers' bookings.",
    "They propose a route-based approximate dynamic programming approach to tackle the challenges such as finding feasible time windows for an incoming customer, estimating the opportunity costs and optimizing the time window prices in real time.",
    "Asdemir et al. (2009) examined online groceries and the costs of home delivery operations.",
    "The authors developed a Markov decision process-based model to determine the optimal price based on customer choices.",
    "Another group of authors (Klein et al., 2008) proposed an approach based on mixed-integer linear programming for online retailers with home delivery business models."
  ]
}